programme.desc: Miao Miao is an awkward young beauty who nevertheless enchants her outgoing classmate Xiao Ai. However, Miao Miao discovers her own burgeoning attraction to a sullen CD store owner, and quietly pursues him.

programme.title: Born To Fly
programme.desc: Lei Yu has officially become the new generation of Chinese test pilots after rounds of strict selection. Captain Zhang Ting leads Lei Yu and other pilots to test the latest fighter jets.

programme.title: Once Upon A Time In Hong Kong
programme.desc: A police sergeant teams up with a triad boss to make billions of dollars in bribes. As a lawyer joins his friend in ICAC, the battle between the righteous and the wicked has just begun.

programme.title: Tales From The Occult
programme.desc: An old school anthology consisting of three short films, Tales from the Occult is the first in a new omnibus series about the hidden horrors that lurk behind the urban landscape of Hong Kong.

programme.title: 77 Heartwarmings
programme.desc: After breaking up with Adam, Eva focuses on her career but Adam still wants to make up and tries to move her 77 times. Will Adam succeed in warming Eva's heart?

programme.title: Septet: The Story Of Hong Kong
programme.desc: Seven of Hong Kong's most revered directors, all with distinctly unique styles, come together for the first time to compose a symphony of stories for their city from the 50s to the future.

programme.title: Moscow Mission
programme.desc: A gang of criminals commits a heist, stealing cash and goods from the cross border train. A Chinese police officer takes charge of the operation to arrest the criminals, but uncovers a bigger conspiracy instead.

programme.title: Acting Out Of Love
programme.desc: Wei Hung Jen is a struggling actor. Hui Hsin, the associate producer, must write a script for a love story so as to get a reference letter to study scriptwriting overseas. Later Jen falls for Hui.

programme.title: Bodies At Rest
programme.desc: When three armed criminals barge into a morgue, a forensic doctor and his student must fight with their lives to stop the criminals from obtaining a bullet from inside a corpse that is a key piece of evidence.

programme.title: Touch Of The Light
programme.desc: A blind but talented pianist Siang encounters an unrecognized but skilful dancer Chieh. Chieh is attracted to the courageous Siang while Siang is fascinated by the adventurous Chieh.

programme.title: Call Me Agent
programme.desc: One day, Miu Ling rescues an injured secret agent who promises to make her his apprentice. From then on, her life is turned upside down and she goes onto a roller-coaster of madcap adventures.

programme.title: Dummy Mommy, Without A Baby
programme.desc: Fong Lai Kuen works at an advertising agency but is about to be sacked by her boss after offending him. She pretends to be pregnant so that the company cannot fire her, according to the labour law.

programme.title: The Italian Recipe
programme.desc: Famous pop idol Peng travels to Rome for a reality show and encounters an ordinary girl, Mang, who dreams of becoming a great chef after migrating to Italy. Their lives begin to change as the two start to fall in love.

programme.title: Fallen Angels
programme.desc: The funkier cousin to Chungking Express, director Wong Kar Wai looks at five fallen angels who suffer love and loss amidst the crime and chaos of Hong Kong's neon nights.

programme.title: Love Is Blind, Hate Too
programme.desc: Bo lost her eye sight in a serious car accident a year ago. One day, an intruder enters Bo's house and takes her hostage. Then, she discovers her husband's secret which is related to her accident last year.

programme.title: Till We Meet Again
programme.desc: Ng Ka Wai is hoping that he will see his loving mother Mui again one day. When his lost memory suddenly returns, he recalls what he has done to his mother, an unforgivable sin leading to the 10-year separation.

programme.title: See You Tomorrow
programme.desc: Chen and his partner Guan are legendary 'navigators', but in the process of helping a girl Xiao Yu, they must also face their own problems.

programme.title: Lonely Eighteen
programme.desc: Elaine and her best friend Ying enter the entertainment industry hoping to change their fates from poverty. When show business declines after a decade, their choices lead them to two different paths in life.

programme.title: A Murder Erased
programme.desc: Police officer Choi is assigned to a death scene investigation where the deceased body had laid undiscovered for eight years. A prosecutor who joins the investigation finds Choi's actions suspicious.

programme.title: Flirting Scholar 2
programme.desc: The movie tells the story of Tang Bo Hu who encounters a beautiful girl when studying in a monastery. But her hidden identity is accidentally unveiled when Tang and friends uncover a conspiracy at the monastery.

programme.title: Born To Fly
programme.desc: Lei Yu has officially become the new generation of Chinese test pilots after rounds of strict selection. Captain Zhang Ting leads Lei Yu and other pilots to test the latest fighter jets.

programme.title: Somewhere Winter
programme.desc: The film follows the love story of a university student, An Ran and a Taiwanese man, Qi Xiao. They met and fell in love with each other in Beijing in 1991, at a concert by Chyi Chin, a Taiwanese singer.

programme.title: Project Gutenberg
programme.desc: The Hong Kong police hunt for a counterfeiting gang led by a mastermind known as Painter. In an effort to find Painter's real identity, the police recruits artist Lee Man to assist in solving the case.

programme.title: Table For Six
programme.desc: Three brothers reside in a home inherited from their late parents. The eldest brother insists they have dinner at home every night as a family, but tensions begin to rise when their girlfriends join in as well.

programme.title: The Rescue
programme.desc: An emergency occurs on an offshore drilling rig that would cause it to capsize and sink. The Emergency Response Unit races against the clock in a chopper rescue mission amidst dangerous explosions and fire.

programme.title: Bodyguards And Assassins
programme.desc: Chinese revolutionary leader Sun Yat-sen returned to Hong Kong for further plans of overthrowing the Qing Dynasty. Businessman Li and Chan found 4 bodyguards to protect Mr Sun for the assassination of the Qing Dynasty.

programme.title: Mr. McDreamy
programme.desc: An affluent second generation rich man squanders his parents' money and calls himself Mr McDreamy. When his parents finally had enough of him and disowned him, he decides to establish a 'Mr McDreamy Training Academy'.

programme.title: Detective Vs. Sleuths
programme.desc: Former top detective Lee vows to bring a group of killers who calls themselves 'The Chosen Sleuths' to justice for a series of cold-blooded murders whose victims are runaway suspects of unsolved cases.

programme.title: Whatever You Want
programme.desc: Anita Yuan Yung-yi stars as an illegitimate daughter who inadvertently finds a pearl with a genie in it. Michael Wong is the genie who gives her three wishes, leading to a lot of hilarity and even a little heartbreak.

programme.title: My Kung Fu Sweetheart
programme.desc: Phoenix's parents are martial arts superheroes, who hide their true identities while ferreting out evil martial artists. She gets trained in the misty mountains, where she learns of her all-important romantic destiny.

programme.title: Everything Under Control
programme.desc: During a diamond heist, one of the security escorts, Jelly, steals the diamonds and flees. Fellow security escorts, Yau Shing and Penguin, are forced to help the robber track down the diamonds.

programme.title: Endgame
programme.desc: A killer and a stage actor accidentally swapped their identities at a bathhouse. When the killer strives to become a successful stage actor, he also starts to recall what has happened.

programme.title: The Bare-Footed Kid
programme.desc: A young man arrives in the city to work with the friend of his dead father. When their dye shop is burnt down by a local strongman, he decides to fight back to protect all of them and save the shop.

programme.title: Hell Hole
programme.desc: About three horror stories in different era: a pregnant woman haunted by a ghost, a boy commits suicide, and some company staff are haunted after they open a box of used clothes.

programme.title: Those Were The Days
programme.desc: Director Wong despises Cantonese movies of the 60s, but accidentally travels back in time to that movie set. He meets Director Chu, who tells him he can return to modern time if someone likes the film he makes.

programme.title: Lovers Blades
programme.desc: Forbidden love and magical weapons are at the centre of this enjoyable martial arts comedy. A reunited couple must recover the titular swords and avenge a murder from their past!

programme.title: The Bride Napping
programme.desc: A rich girl Yue Ying, together with her maid Chun Lan, encounter a poor scholar Bian Ji at a fete. Chun Lan realizes Yue Ying is in love with him, but mixes his identity with a bandit due to an old servant's confusion.

programme.title: Tropicana Interlude
programme.desc: Ping and Su are lovers who operate a travel agency specializing in Southeast Asian holidays. Tung, a school mistress, and her students join a guided tour lead by Ping.

programme.title: The Anonymous Heroes
programme.desc: Two young men join a rebel group after the Chinese Revolution of 1911 and become patriotic heroes accidentally. Assisted by a warlord's daughter, they successfully help the rebels steal weapons from the warlord.

programme.title: The Warlord
programme.desc: A bandit became a warlord in the northern China by helping Russia fight against Japan. The warlord was finally killed by the daughter of a troupe master whom he had killed for no reason.

programme.title: The Magnificent Ruffians
programme.desc: A gang of unemployed martial artists seem to have their bad fortunes turned when the head of a local security agency hires them to take out the competition and take each other on until the end.

programme.title: Love Without End
programme.desc: Lin Dai stars as a nightclub singer who falls for a young architect. When he suffers grave financial difficulty, she does the unthinkable to help him.

programme.title: One Way Only
programme.desc: Acclaimed actor Danny Lee plays a motorbike workshop owner who injured during an illegal motorcycle race and continues to race regardless of the physical consequences and the law.

programme.title: The Venus' Tear Diamond
programme.desc: Legendary rival jewel thieves Fragrant Night and Nocturnal Earl travel to Japan to steal the famous Venus' Tear Diamond.

programme.title: Kid From Kwangtung
programme.desc: When an Anti-Ching chief is killed, his family flees to a small town populated by quarreling students and formidable gym coaches. However, one teacher is also an undercover agent.

programme.title: The Emperor And The Minister
programme.desc: The Emperor Qianlong is not the legitimate successor to the throne at birth, but he only learns the truth when two senior members of a subversive anti-government secret organisation contact him years later.

programme.title: Man Of Iron
programme.desc: Chou Lian Huan is good at fist fighting in Shanghai. In order to please a hostess named Chen Ju Fang, he is willing to sacrifice everything and fight against the son of the gang leader in Shanghai.

programme.title: The Last Tempest
programme.desc: This sequel to The Empress Dowager continues the tale of Emperor Guangxu and Empress Dowager Cixi. Despite Guangxu's enthronement, his ability to rule effectively is overshadowed by the ever-present power of Cixi.

programme.title: The Bloody Escape
programme.desc: Ku is a skilled Kung Fu artist brought up by the bandits and does not agree with the brutal leader of the bandit's camp. He rescues Tong, a young lady forced to become the leader's wife.

programme.title: Hong Kong Rhapsody
programme.desc: Hong Kong Rhapsody is a musical extravaganza full of song and dance. Peter Chen-Ho stars as a playboy magician who changes his ways after he becomes the guardian of a young singer.

programme.title: The Lady Hermit
programme.desc: The Lady Hermit hides away for years to plot revenge after being defeated by the evil Black Knight. Young swordswoman Tsui Ping is determined to take down Black Knight herself and begs to teach her martial arts skills.

programme.title: Danger Has Two Faces
programme.desc: Many years ago, Inspector Kam killed an innocent man and decided to resign from the police force. He became a professional killer who disguises as a pet store owner.

programme.title: Let's Fall In Love
programme.desc: Legendary actress Lin Feng Jiao stars in this romantic comedy as an unlikely romance occurs between an entrepreneur's son and a kindergarten's principal's niece.

programme.title: Vengeance Is A Golden Blade
programme.desc: Convoy Master Li's wife has an affair with his rival Long, who plans to steal Li's Golden Blade and kill him as well as his young daughter.

programme.title: Asia-Pol
programme.desc: Asiapol agent Yang Ming Xuan trails a shipment of contraband gold being delivered to gang leader, George Eaton. He enlists the help of a Chinese woman who is trying to avenge her sister.

programme.title: Vengeance
programme.desc: Yu Lou is betrayed by his wife and eventually killed by her lover, Fung, who is the boss of a martial arts school. Yu Lou's brother, Xiao Lou, knows about his tragic death and is determined to take revenge for him.

programme.title: Apartment For Ladies
programme.desc: Betty Ting Pei plays a Taiwanese singer who comes to Hong Kong in search of her missing sister, narrowly avoids getting raped by a street gang and is rescued by a handsome composer.

programme.title: The Villains
programme.desc: Young Lin Hsiao-hung is a poor orphan. She seeks the help of her wealthy uncle, Fang Chen-chuan and his sons, Fang Cheng who is brave and honest, and Fang Feng, a playboy.

programme.title: Two Con Men
programme.desc: A wonderfully twisted, pseudo-romantic comedy starring Liang Tien and Chang Ying in an age-old competition between rookie con artist versus the ultimate, experienced flimflam man.

programme.title: Disciples Of Shaolin
programme.desc: Yi is a skilled disciple of the Hong Quan style kung fu who work in a textile mill recommended by his senior, Han. Han warns Yi not to show off his martial arts skill so as to avoid getting into trouble.

programme.title: The Story Of Sue San
programme.desc: Wang is the son of a respected government official whereas Sue San is a famous prostitute. Although they love each other and seem to be perfectly matched, the two are worlds apart when it comes to social ranking.

programme.title: The Silver Fox
programme.desc: Lily Ho portrays the feared swordswoman Silver Fox, who witnessed her father senselessly wounded and her mother raped. 18 years later it's payback time.

programme.title: Have Sword Will Travel
programme.desc: When the head of a manor loses his kung fu skills, he enlists his nephew and his fiance to help escort gold to the capital. The duo run into a mysterious knight along the way and prevent bandits from stealing the gold.

programme.title: The Adulteress
programme.desc: In the waning day of the Ching Dynasty, the son of the local magistrate murdered a peddler and raped his wife. The wife had been framed for her husband's murder by the rapist.

programme.title: The Purple Shell
programme.desc: Hui Pui-ching is often ill-treated by her husband Fan Pak-nan, a cruel and uncouth man. At a party, Pui-ching meets rich and erudite businessman, Ha Mon-hin and they are mutually attracted.

programme.title: The Water Margin
programme.desc: Chang Cheh's The Water Margin is the martial arts epic of epics. Based on the true legend of how 108 rebels in the mountains were able to repeatedly defeat invading Sung armies.

programme.title: The Pure And The Evil
programme.desc: What began as the sweet reunion of two high school friends quickly deteriorates into a deranged erotic nightmare when Rose takes a shine to former classmate Fang and her new fiance!

programme.title: Heroes Shed No Tears
programme.desc: Alexander Fu Sheng plays a man who is supposed to die at the hand of a sword with a teardrop forged onto the blade.

programme.title: The Kingdom And The Beauty
programme.desc: Starlet Linda Lin Dai gives an acclaimed performance as a country girl who embarks on a forbidden relationship with Emperor Cheng-Te, whom she would love for the rest of her life.

programme.title: The Twelve Gold Medallions
programme.desc: The evil minister uses the twelve golden medallions, the highest imperial decree, to summon war hero Yueh Fei back from the frontline and execute him. A group of wandering warriors try to stop the medallion couriers.

programme.title: Songfest
programme.desc: Shot on location at Taiwan's beautiful Sun-Moon Lake, it's the turbulent romance of a passionate tea picker and a debonair fisherman.

programme.title: The Convict Killer
programme.desc: A framed kung-fu master seeks revenge after 15 years in prison. He survives one attempt on his life after another! An intriguing, exciting production which weaves mystery and suspense with kung-fu action.

programme.title: Love With The Perfect Stranger
programme.desc: After breaking up with his girlfriend, salesman Bao meets a rich girl, Jin Jin, who just broke up with her boyfriend. Two equally heartbroken strangers fall in love instantly and get married on impulse.

programme.title: Descendant Of The Sun
programme.desc: A magic solar baby is sent Earthbound by a benevolent god and raised by an old carpenter. He has martial arts superpowers and ''green kryptonite'' loses them during solar eclipses.

programme.title: Fast Fingers
programme.desc: After his release from prison, Uncle Bill returns to make a fortune with his past thieving partners. They continue to prey on the unsuspecting public, but are closely watched by the upright police chief.

programme.title: The Crazy Bumpkins
programme.desc: This side-splitting comedy sees naive Ah Niu head to HK, where he is repeatedly exploited and taken advantage of, and eventually finds himself arrested and imprisoned.

programme.title: Twelve Deadly Coins
programme.desc: When Qiao Miao is about to kill the bandit whom he just met, he is attracted by her beauty and they quickly fall in love. The two later discover the blood feud between the owner of the unique weapon.

programme.title: The Deadly Knives
programme.desc: Martial arts student Yen returns to defend the family homestead against Japanese financiers. Once back, Yen faces romantic complications as well as marauding, murderers villains.

programme.title: West Chamber
programme.desc: The story is based on a famous Chinese opera. A young impoverished scholar, Zhang, is enchanted by Hong, the daughter of an influential family whom he meets in a temple.

programme.title: The Winged Tiger
programme.desc: If the two big villains Winged Tiger and Underworld King join forces, the martial arts world will be plunged into chaos. The union is set to occur with the marriage of the Underworld King's sister and the Winged Tiger.

programme.title: Three Sinners
programme.desc: Based on the classic Ming Dynasty novel The Water Margin, Three Sinners is a Huangmei Opera about love, betrayal, murder, and redemption.

programme.title: The Flying Guillotine
programme.desc: Ma Teng is one of the 'Flying Guillotine Squad', a group of killers commissioned by the Emperor Yung. When he starts to question the morality of his missions, he becomes a fugitive hunted by his former comrades.

programme.title: Hex Vs Witchcraft
programme.desc: Yu Nan (Yi Lei) is a compulsive gambler. He makes his wife as a down payment for his debt, feeling regretted and decides to kill himself but stops when a beautiful ghost appears.

programme.title: Return To The 36th Chamber
programme.desc: The second film of the trilogy, Gordon Liu plays Zhou Ren Jie, a man who impersonates a monk in order to learn kung fu in Shaolin, and eventually creates his own Shaolin style of 'scaffolding kung fu'.

programme.title: Spring Blossoms
programme.desc: Some of Shaw Brothers' biggest female stars of the 1970s share the screen in this tale of young love and interfering parents, starring Lily Li, Shu Pei Pei and Essie Lin Chia.

programme.title: The Secret Of The Dirk
programme.desc: The inhabitants of the City of Liu are forced to flee when the vicious Black Tigers gang raids their city, but are able to hide all their gold and treasures in a valley.

programme.title: The Yellow Muffler
programme.desc: Japanese director Inoue Umetsugu depicts the glamourous world of nightclub performers in this story about two struggling sisters, played by Irene Chen Yi Ling and Betty Ting Pei.

programme.title: Super Inframan
programme.desc: Transformed from a young laboratory researcher, the thunderbolt-fisted Inframan must battle Princess Dragon Mom who wakes up from hibernation to conquer the earth with her army of mutant monsters.

programme.title: The Grand Substitution
programme.desc: This Huangmei Opera epic stars Li Li-hua and Ivy Ling Po in the story of a loyal Imperial Court servant who gives up his own newborn son to save the prince from an evil official.
